<caption>
    <formalpara>
        <title>Figure 1. The <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=DBL-1;class=protein" role="_blank">DBL-1</ulink>/TGF-<symbol role= "symbolfont">&#x03B2;</symbol> pathway</title>
<para>Binding of the TGF-<symbol role= "symbolfont">&#x03B2;</symbol>-like ligand to the heterodimeric <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=DAF-4;class=protein" role="_blank">DAF-4</ulink>/<ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=SMA-6;class=protein" role="_blank">SMA-6</ulink> receptor leads to the phosphorylation and activation of the SMAD proteins <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=SMA-2;class=protein" role="_blank">SMA-2</ulink>, <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=SMA-3;class=protein" role="_blank">SMA-3</ulink> and <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=SMA-4;class=protein" role="_blank">SMA-4</ulink>. They translocate into the nucleus where they can activate gene expression, in some cases in association with <ulink url="http://www.wormbase.org/db/seq/protein?name=SMA-9;class=protein" role="_blank">SMA-9</ulink>.</para>
    </formalpara>
</caption>